---
// src/pages/disclosure.astro
// Full affiliate disclosure page (FTC compliance)

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure – FunWithKidsBoston"
  description="Full affiliate disclosure for FunWithKidsBoston.com. Learn how we use affiliate links from Amazon Associates, Viator, and other programs."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-6">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>

    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p><em>Last updated: January 2025</em></p>

      <p>
        At <strong>FunWithKidsBoston.com</strong>, we believe in full transparency with our readers. This page explains how we use affiliate links and how they support our mission to bring you the best family-friendly content for the Greater Boston area.
      </p>

      <h2>What Are Affiliate Links?</h2>
      <p>
        Some of the links on this website are "affiliate links." This means that if you click on the link and purchase an item, FunWithKidsBoston will receive an affiliate commission at no additional cost to you. The price you pay is the same whether you use the affiliate link or go directly to the vendor's website.
      </p>

      <h2>Amazon Associates Program</h2>
      <p>
        FunWithKidsBoston.com is a participant in the <strong>Amazon Services LLC Associates Program</strong>, an affiliate advertising program designed to provide a means for sites to earn advertising fees by advertising and linking to <strong>Amazon.com</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        As an Amazon Associate, we earn from qualifying purchases. Product prices and availability are accurate as of the date/time of publication and are subject to change. Any price and availability information displayed on Amazon at the time of purchase will apply to the purchase of the product.
      </p>

      <h2>Viator Affiliate Program</h2>
      <p>
        We also participate in the <strong>Viator affiliate program</strong>. When we recommend tours, activities, and experiences, we may include Viator affiliate links. If you book through these links, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.
      </p>

      <h2>Other Affiliate Partnerships</h2>
      <p>
        From time to time, we may participate in other affiliate programs or partnerships with brands and services that are relevant to families in the Boston area. We will always disclose these relationships in our content.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Promise to You</h2>
      <p>
        We want you to know that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>We <strong>only recommend products, services, and experiences</strong> that we have personally used or thoroughly researched and genuinely believe will benefit families.</li>
        <li>Our editorial content is <strong>not influenced</strong> by affiliate partnerships. We write honest reviews and guides regardless of whether we earn a commission.</li>
        <li>We clearly mark affiliate links in our posts with a disclosure notice at the beginning of each article that contains them.</li>
        <li>Your trust is our highest priority. If we ever recommend something, it's because we truly believe it will enhance your family's experience.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>FTC Compliance</h2>
      <p>
        In accordance with the <strong>Federal Trade Commission (FTC)</strong> guidelines, we disclose our affiliate relationships to ensure full transparency. The FTC requires that we clearly identify any relationship we have with product manufacturers, service providers, or other entities when we receive compensation for promoting their products or services.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions?</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about our affiliate relationships or this disclosure, please don't hesitate to contact us at <strong>hello@funwithkidsboston.com</strong>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Thank you for supporting FunWithKidsBoston! Your clicks and purchases help us keep creating free family guides for the Boston community. 🎉
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>